  "title": "First Love",
  "description": "First Love is a poetic reflection on a misanthropic outcast's relationship with love — particularly with a woman named Lulu, who he encountered on the canal-side bench that was once his nocturnal home. This darkly comic short story by Samuel Beckett explores love, death and one man's inability to comprehend humanity.",
